🔷 Explanation of Architecture
🔹 1. Users
End users access the application through a browser.
Requests are sent to the Load Balancer.
🔹 2. Application Load Balancer
Distributes incoming traffic across multiple EC2 instances.
Ensures high availability and fault tolerance.
🔹 3. EC2 Instances (Web Servers)
Run Apache/Nginx web server.
Host your application.
Instances are created dynamically using Auto Scaling.
🔹 4. Auto Scaling Group
Maintains minimum and maximum number of instances (2–4).
Automatically:
Adds instances when load increases
Removes instances when load decreases
🔹 5. Launch Template
Defines configuration for new instances:
AMI
Instance type
Security group
🔹 6. AMI (Amazon Machine Image)
Pre-configured image of your application server.
Used to launch identical EC2 instances.
🔹 7. Base EC2 Instance
Initial server where:
Apache installed
App deployed
Used to create AMI
🔹 8. GitHub
Stores your application code
Code is cloned into EC2 instance
🔷 Monitoring Section
🔹 9. CloudWatch
Monitors system performance (CPU usage)
Collects metrics from EC2 instances
🔹 10. CloudWatch Alarms
Triggered when CPU crosses threshold
Example:
CPU > 70% → Scale Out
CPU < 30% → Scale In
🔹 11. SNS (Simple Notification Service)
Sends alerts when alarms trigger
🔹 12. Email Notifications
You receive alerts about:
High CPU usage
Scaling events
